\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 #### **Create Comprehensive Documentation (4 hours)**
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ```markdown
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 # Phase 5: Guideline Library - User Guide
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## Overview
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 The Guideline Library provides complete evidence traceability for all clinical recommendations in the CDS system.
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## Architecture
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ```
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Recommendation \uc0\u8594  Protocol Action \u8594  Guideline Recommendation \u8594  Research Evidence
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ```
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## Key Features
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### 1. Evidence Chain
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Every recommendation includes:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Source guideline (e.g., SSC 2021)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Specific guideline recommendation (e.g., "Measure lactate within 1 hour")
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Recommendation strength (Strong, Weak, Conditional)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Evidence quality (High, Moderate, Low, Very Low)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Supporting research studies (PMIDs)
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### 2. Quality Assessment
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Uses GRADE methodology:
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **High**: Multiple high-quality RCTs or meta-analyses
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **Moderate**: RCTs with limitations or strong observational evidence
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **Low**: Observational studies or low-quality RCTs
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **Very Low**: Expert opinion or case series
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### 3. Currency Monitoring
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Automatically flags outdated guidelines (>5 years)
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Alerts when evidence needs review
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - Tracks superseded guidelines
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## Usage Examples
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### Get Evidence for Action
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ```java
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ProtocolAction action = protocol.getAction("SEPSIS-LAB-001");
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 EvidenceChain chain = guidelineLinker.getEvidenceChain(action);
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 System.out.println("Guideline: " + chain.getSourceGuideline().getShortName());
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 System.out.println("Strength: " + chain.getGuidelineRecommendation().getStrength());
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 System.out.println("Quality: " + chain.getOverallQuality());
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ```
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### Validate Protocol Compliance
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ```java
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Protocol protocol = protocolLoader.getProtocol("SEPSIS-SSC-2021");
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 Guideline guideline = guidelineLoader.getGuideline("GUIDE-SSC-2021");
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ValidationReport report = guidelineLinker.validateProtocol(protocol, guideline);
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 System.out.println("Compliance: " + report.getCompliancePercentage() + "%");
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ```
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### Display Evidence Trail
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ```java
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 String trail = chain.getEvidenceTrail();
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 // Outputs complete hierarchy: Action \uc0\u8594  Guideline \u8594  Recommendation \u8594  Evidence
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ```
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## Adding New Guidelines
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 1. Create YAML file in `guidelines/\{specialty\}/`
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 2. Use existing guidelines as template
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 3. Link recommendations to protocol actions via `linkedProtocolActions`
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 4. Cite evidence using PMIDs in `keyEvidence`
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 5. Load and validate
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## Quality Indicators
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **\uc0\u55357 \u57314  STRONG**: High-quality evidence + strong recommendation
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **\uc0\u55357 \u57313  MODERATE**: Moderate evidence + weak recommendation
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **\uc0\u55357 \u57312  WEAK**: Low-quality evidence or expert opinion
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - **\uc0\u9888 \u65039  OUTDATED**: Evidence >5 years old or superseded guideline
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ## API Reference
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### GuidelineLinker
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - `getEvidenceChain(action)` - Get complete evidence trail
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - `getSourceGuideline(action)` - Get source guideline
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - `getEvidence(action)` - Get supporting citations
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - `validateProtocol(protocol, guideline)` - Check compliance
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - `assessOverallQuality(chain)` - GRADE assessment
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### GuidelineLoader
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - `loadAllGuidelines()` - Load all from resources
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - `getGuideline(id)` - Get by ID
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - `getCurrentGuidelines()` - Get non-superseded only
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - `getGuidelinesBySpecialty(specialty)` - Filter by specialty
\f1\fs24 \
\

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ### CitationLoader
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - `loadCitation(pmid)` - Load by PMID
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 - `fetchFromPubMed(pmid)` - Fetch from PubMed API
\f1\fs24 \

\f0\fs29\fsmilli14667 ```
\f1\fs24 \
\

